b'When your home becomes your office, it can be easy to get stuck in a rut and not feel quite as motivated as usual. Switching it up and moving to a different workspace every couple hours gives you the chance to stretch your legs and refocus. Your tires, believe it or not, also need a change every now and again to avoid any uneven wear \xe2\x80\x93 we recommend you rotate them every 5000 to 7000 miles. #MitsuSelfMaintenance'

b'Chances are you\xe2\x80\x99re not drinking enough water (almost nobody does!). Give your body and mind the hydration it needs and try to drink a bit more water every day. With your mind sharp and hydrated, it\xe2\x80\x99ll be easier to remember that your car needs fluids too \xe2\x80\x93 but definitely not water! Take the time every couple weeks to check the coolant or antifreeze, brake fluid, transmission fluid, windshield washer fluid, power steering fluid and oil. #MitsuSelfMaintenance'

b'Owning your lockdown diet is tough when your pantry is full of snacks and easy-prep, low-nutrient foods. To keep in good shape and health, stock up (safely and by practicing social distancing ) on leafy greens and healthy food. What goes into your car is just as important \xe2\x80\x93 change your oil on a regular basis to keep your car in tip top shape. #MitsuSelfMaintenance'

b'It\xe2\x80\x99s easy to get bogged down by social media negativity and non-stop bad news at the moment. Wipe away both the news cycle negativity from your mind and inclement weather from your windshield to keep yourself positive and focused on the present. #MitsuSelfMaintenance'

b'Peak performance doesn\xe2\x80\x99t happen by magic \xe2\x80\x93 it takes regular maintenance and care. Keeping your car running smoothly can be as simple as checking your spark plugs every 30k miles, while staying sharp mentally might just take some new hobbies and interests. #MitsuSelfMaintenance'

b'Keeping active can be difficult at the moment but try to exercise regularly (in keeping with government advice) and make sure you and your Mitsubishi get a much-needed breath of fresh air by checking your air filter every 15k miles. #MitsuSelfMaintenance'

b'Working from home comes with its own challenges, like losing track of the work/play balance. If you swing too far towards work, you might find yourself burnt out. Just like proper car battery maintenance, it\xe2\x80\x99s important to take care of yourself and keep your batteries charged up. #MitsuSelfMaintenance'

b'It\xe2\x80\x99s easy to forget if it\xe2\x80\x99s a Monday, Sunday or anything in between if you\xe2\x80\x99re wearing the same thing every day. Keeping routines \xe2\x80\x93 like getting dressed every day \xe2\x80\x93 can help keep things feeling that much more normal. Other good habits, like regularly checking your Mitsubishi\xe2\x80\x99s belts and hoses for cracks or damage are equally important because one day soon you\xe2\x80\x99ll be back behind the wheel. #MitsuSelfMaintenance'

b'Everyone knows how important car maintenance is, but in this difficult time, we believe maintenance means more than looking after your car. Introducing Mitsubishi\xe2\x80\x99s Self Care x Car Care tips, helping you to stay in peak condition. We know leaving your home isn\xe2\x80\x99t ideal, which is why our dealerships are offering touchless service and assistance if your Mitsubishi needs maintenance that goes beyond your DIY skills. #MitsuSelfMaintenance'
